Hier ist gerade jemand, der meinen Küchenboden repariert. Und ich tu jetzt so, als hätte ich noch einen Job und würde von zu Hause aus arbeiten, während ich an Too Hot to Handle sitze.
Wenn ich es verdammt nochmal schaffen würde, die Datei zu öffnen. (Scheiß One Drive.)
*Stimme eines Hackers* Ich bin drin.
Und genau da fängt er an, super laut zu bohren. Hurra.
Es fühlt sich unangenehm passiv-aggressiv an, meinen Luftreiniger bis zum Anschlag aufzudrehen, aber ich kann den Holzstaub riechen, daher wäre es sogar völlig ok, auch wenn er kein Maskengegner wäre. Und muss ich mich wirklich schützen?
I would really like to go back to bed, but I can't before he's gone.
At least I finally finished revising Chapter 4!
Chapter five is long, but so damn terrifying. Oh yes, that's the good stuff!
I'm doing a search and replace for … ➡️ Ellipsis symbol and there are 54 in this chapter 😅
No, I'll stick with it. Natural language is usually choppy, especially when one gets emotional.
The handyperson is now using the vacuum cleaner. Hopefully, that means he'll be finished soon.
He went outside to cut something (it sounds like that's what it is). I secretly checked how far he had gotten. There's still a lot to do :(
Still 7 pages left in Chapter 5. It's still my favorite chapter and it's quite tidy – mostly changes to the text and very small corrections to direct speech, and I need to make everything a bit more concise. But I really could use a break and a tea, but the guy is still in my kitchen.
Now he's started vacuuming again. Hopefully, that's a good sign.
The kitchen guy is gone!
He told me that he had made a cost estimate for the entire floor, but the landlords were too tight and only paid for the part next to the door that is no longer in order. Feels much better now.
The house is well-ventilated and my air purifier is running in the kitchen, while I'm having a tea in the garden!
